@neilcsmith-net This is related to #1314. So we should fix this in NB11.2, I think. Is it OK?
@tmysik If it's OK with Neil and you approve it, please merge this.

BTW, https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NETBEANS-3085 is fixed. So, all unit tests pass.

Thanks!

@junichi11 My bad, I overlooked that @neilcsmith-net is as a reviewer too - that is information I know I need to look for the next time! Sorry guys!

@neilcsmith-net 

> If there's not a green tick by all reviewers at top right, please don't assume it's OK to merge

Now I will know. Sorry for missing it. No idea whether it is possible but - can we allow PR to be merged only when all the reviewers agree? In such a case, I won't be able to merge this PR (and probably force you to approve it so I can merge ;)

@neilcsmith-net 

> https://help.github.com/en/articles/about-pull-request-reviews

I would expect something like `Allow merge only if all reviewers approved` checkbox in the repository settings. But that is not the case if I understand it correctly. Using a fixed number of reviewers does not seem to me to be much useful (maybe for companies it can work well?).
